   <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">This document describes how to replace a failed Digi Edgeport model 416 DB-25, on a COMSOC
         1 Interface. The procedure helps to mitigate a problem with TCP/IP communication indicated
         when frequent COM-SOC II error messages occur during automatic or manual Saves from the
         sections (not MOC Save). If the FSC shares the server with the PIC application (called a
         Combo system), this procedure should not be necessary because it is part of every upgrade.
         Consult the personnel responsible for the PIC to determine when the procedure was last
         performed.</p>
